Curiously Recurring Template Pattern (CRTP) is when a class `Derived` inherits from a class template instantiated with `Derived` itself:

```
template <typename Derived>
class Base {
public:
 void interface() {
 // static polymorphism: we call into Derived without virtual
 static_cast<Derived *>(this)->implementation();
 }
};

class Derived : public Base<Derived> {
public:
 void implementation() { /* ... */ }
};
```

MLIR operations are normally defined with:

